cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about designing a pedestrian detector using a new cascade design procedure that combines features of vastly different complexities, including the responses of a deep convolutional neural network (CNN). Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a boosting algorithm to solve the optimization problem, which could fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the pedestrian detector is designed to work in real-world scenarios, which could be related to robotics (cs.RO).
